BMC NIC: Set BMC NIC_ Configured the current BMC network to Dedicated NIC_
IOAT2: IOAT2_ Enabled support for Intel I_O Acceleration Technology_
Execute Disable: Execute_Disable Bit Capability Execute_Disable Bit Capability_ Enabled allowing memory to be marked as executable or non_executable_ whencombined with a supporting operating system_
BMC IP SRC: BMC IP address source_ Configured the current BMC IP address to be a specified static address_
F1 Error: Wait For _Fl If Error_ Disabled the BIOS from prompting for F1 on error_
Quiet Boot: Quiet Boot_ Disabled the display of the splash or summary screen_ The user is able to see the detail of the POST messages_
QPI Bandwidth Priority: Intel QPI Bandwidth Priority_ Configured the priority of requests on the QPI bus for computational traffic_
NIC2 ROM: NIC 2 OptIon ROM_ Enabled onboard Intel 82576 NIC port 2 option ROM_
Video Controller: On_board Video Controller_ Enabled on_board video device_
IPMI Detect: IPMI Detection_ Enabled making BMC device can be detected by 05es which support PnP and IPMI drivers_
Processor Cores: Active Processor Cores_ Configured number of cores to enable in each processor package_
Force PXE: Force PXE First_ Enabled force PXE devices to be the first boot devices_
NIC1 ROM: NIC 1 OptIon ROM_ Enabled onboard Intel 82576 NIC port 1 option ROM_
NIC PXE: NIC Function Support_ Configured NIC function for PXE support_
Hyper Threading: Hyper_Threading Technology _HT__ Enabled Intel Hyper_Threading Technology_
AC Power: Restore on AC Power Loss_ Configured system power recovery behavior as Power On after restoring on AC power loss
Quick Bookt: Quick Boot_ Enabled allowing BIOS to skip certain tests while POST_
NUMA: NUMA Support Enabled node interleaving for processors to have asymmetric access to local and remote memory_
